The Propellant Managment Devices
In the experiment we will test 8 different PMDs in small tanks. For the fluid we will use normal water combined with Uranin. In the slide show below you can see first 3D-printed prototypes filled with Uranin to test the observation capabilities of our camera.

&lt; &gt;

Next steps
This collaborative effort allows us to gather valuable insights and refine our design for optimal performance. Stay tuned for updates on the BEARS Instagram page, where we will share behind-the-scenes glimpses and exciting milestones. Our timeline targets the completion of the test stand by the end of 2024. We understand that reaching for the stars requires meticulous planning, dedication, and collaboration, and we’re thrilled to have you join us on this exciting journey.

&lt; &gt;

Our team
In the rocket systems group we build our own rockets. We have already achieved a successful launch to an altitude of 600m. Currently we are building a rocket that is designed to reach an altitude of 3 km. On this also a small experiment is to be accomplished. We also want to participate in competitions with the new rocket.

